1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,009
When you help others feel important, you help yourself feel important, too.

2
00:00:05,679 --> 00:00:14,608
One of the elevator operators who carried me up and down for several months had the look of complete unimportance written all over.

3
00:00:14,879 --> 00:00:19,888
She was fiftiesh, unattractive, and certainly uninspired in her work.

4
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:25,168
It was obvious that her longing to be important was completely unfulfilled.

5
00:00:25,439 --> 00:00:34,929
She was one of the millions of people who live for months at a time without ever being given a reason to believe that someone notices them or cares about them.

6
00:00:35,598 --> 00:00:40,289
One morning, shortly after I became one of her regular uppers and downers,

7
00:00:40,319 --> 00:00:43,009
I noticed that she had had her hair redone.

8
00:00:43,118 --> 00:00:44,529
It was nothing fancy.

9
00:00:44,639 --> 00:00:47,009
It was obviously a homemade job.

10
00:00:47,118 --> 00:00:50,128
But it had been cut and it did look better.

11
00:00:50,399 --> 00:00:54,769
So I said, Miss S. Note, I had learned her name.

12
00:00:55,039 --> 00:00:57,168
I do like what you've done to your hair.

13
00:00:57,279 --> 00:01:03,648
It really looks fine." She blushed, said, thank you, sir, and nearly missed her next stop.

14
00:01:03,919 --> 00:01:05,970
She appreciated the compliment.

15
00:01:07,118 --> 00:01:13,569
Next morning, lo and behold, when I stepped into the elevator I heard, Good morning, Dr. Schwartz.

16
00:01:13,839 --> 00:01:19,009
Not one time before had I heard this operator address anyone by name.

17
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:22,608
And in the remaining months that I had an office in the building,

18
00:01:22,639 --> 00:01:26,128
I never heard anyone called by name except me.

19
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:29,168
I had made the operator feel important.

20
00:01:29,358 --> 00:01:33,250
I had sincerely complimented her and called her by name.

21
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:35,730
I had made her feel important.

22
00:01:35,839 --> 00:01:39,648
Now she was repaying me by making me feel important.

23
00:01:40,159 --> 00:01:41,970
Let's not kid ourselves.

24
00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:48,049
People who do not have a deep-down feeling of self-importance are slated for mediocrity.

25
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:52,049
Again and again, this point must be driven home.

26
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:54,689
You must feel important to succeed.

27
00:01:54,959 --> 00:02:00,449
Helping others to feel important rewards you because it makes you feel more important.

28
00:02:00,799 --> 00:02:02,049
Try it and see.

29
00:02:02,399 --> 00:02:03,730
Here's how to do it.

30
00:02:03,759 --> 00:02:04,929
1.

31
00:02:05,118 --> 00:02:07,009
Practice appreciation.

32
00:02:07,199 --> 00:02:11,569
Make it a rule to let others know you appreciate what they do for you.

33
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:15,490
Never, never let anyone feel he is taken for granted.

34
00:02:15,598 --> 00:02:19,250
Practice appreciation with a warm, sincere smile.

35
00:02:19,519 --> 00:02:24,128
A smile lets others know you notice them and feel kindly toward them.

36
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:29,089
Practice appreciation by letting others know how you depend on them.

37
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:32,929
An earnest, Jim, I don't know what we'd do without you,

38
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:40,289
type of remark makes people feel necessary, and when they feel necessary, they do increasingly better work.

39
00:02:41,118 --> 00:02:45,490
Practice appreciation with honest, personalized compliments.

40
00:02:45,598 --> 00:02:50,689
People thrive on compliments, whether 2 or 20, 9 or 90.

41
00:02:50,799 --> 00:02:52,689
A person craves praise.

42
00:02:52,879 --> 00:02:57,089
He wants to be assured that he's doing a good job, that he is important.

43
00:02:57,279 --> 00:03:01,648
Don't feel that you should hand out praise only for big accomplishments.

44
00:03:01,919 --> 00:03:09,490
Compliment people on little things, their appearance, the way they do their routine work, their ideas, their loyal efforts.

45
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:14,769
Praise by writing personal notes complimenting people you know on their achievements.

46
00:03:14,879 --> 00:03:18,449
Make a special phone call or a special trip to see them.

47
00:03:19,118 --> 00:03:28,608
Don't waste time or mental energy trying to classify people as very important persons, important persons, or unimportant persons.

48
00:03:28,799 --> 00:03:30,368
Make no exceptions.

49
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:36,449
A person, whether he is garbage collector or company vice president, is important to you.

50
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:41,329
Treating someone as second class never gets you first class results.

